Macleane objects to this supposition—-“ that the language of affection is too strong for the short acquaintance which Horace had then enjoyed with Maecenas, and that there is evidence in the poem itself of the Sabine farm having corne into Horace's possession when he wrote it3 but that this did not occur till after the publication of the First Book of Satires is certain, and it is generally referred to A.U.C. 720.”
